plyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3516.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Politics of Erollis Marr *note this is the new threa</span><hr size=1> Good Grief, It wasnt like he got mobs stuck in Befallen and Nejena doors, explioted the hermit in SoK, used pathing problems on Barbarian guards in East K, got up on the wall in Highhold, fought guard in freeport from certain rooftops, or got them stuck in the walls there, or stood in at least 3 dozen spots that I know of where you could hit/cast on mobs and they could not hit you...(99%of these have been &quot;fixed&quot; now BTW)....<br>
<br>
Your going back to the earliest days and anyone playing now who didnt play in the first 6 month to year of this game would have a hard time recognizing thier class.<br>
<br>
Back then Monks and Rogues..well...Sucked, hell rogues didnt even have a working backstab back then! There were zero weapons a monk could use that were &quot;better&quot; than thier hands. there was no &quot;epics&quot; and the top haste item was a FBSS (if you ever even saw one).<br>
 <br>
At the same time the most powerful class BY FAR was the necro. <br>
<br>
why?<br>
 <br>
Because someone discovered that if you gave your pet 2 fine steel daggers it dropped the delay on your pet from ~30 to 19...this combined with Fear ment Necros could pretty well solo anything in the game from about level 39....well anything not in a Dungeon.<br>
<br>
Another great advantage they had back then was the fact they could pull a pet, break a room of lower blues, tell the pet to Guard the room, cast FD and then go to work leaving the game running all day....pets did not poof while Necro's were FD back then, the &quot;hasted&quot; pet would have no problem keeping up with the spawn and even if it was overcome there was no danger to the player (I have a friend who went from 36 to 39 in one day while at work using this &quot;trick&quot;).<br>
<br>
Of course all these &quot;exploits&quot; were nurfed, Necros were brought down rudely from thier god status long ago (I still remember how Shocked Verant was when someone demonstrated that a necro pet WITHOUT the aid of the necro other than pet buffs and FS daggers could solo a level 50 warrior with planer weapons and armour....).<br>
<br>
Face it, there was no way a monk (with the armour and weapons available back then) could keep up to a well played soloing Necro, or Druid for that matter.<br>
<br>
Naele Shadowslayer<br>
60 Shadowknight<br>
Nallae Shadowlsayer<br>
60 Cleric<br>
